"Advertising is pervasive on the Internet these days. It's usually the primary income stream for many of the services, such as Facebook and Google, that we take for granted. But it's also a source of serious threats to our security. Malicious advertising – or ‘malvertising’ – is an increasingly common way for cyber-criminals to either spread malware or lure victims to sites where malware and other scams lurk. And the shift to mobile platforms is only making this problem worse. Advertising is pervasive on the Internet these days. It's usually the primary income stream for many of the services, such as Facebook and Google, that we take for granted. But it's also a source of serious threats to our security. Malicious advertising – or ‘malvertising’ – is an increasingly common way for cyber-criminals to either spread malware or lure victims to sites where malware and other scams lurk. Steve Mansfield-Devine examines the nature of the problem and the (so far) limited responses to it."
